    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main id="main-content">
        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section class="profile-hero" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(224, 33, 138, 0.9) 0%, rgba(199, 21, 133, 0.9) 100%), url('assets/images/placeholder-vp.jpg') center/cover; min-height: 60vh; display: flex; align-items: center; color: white;">
            <div class="container" style="max-width: 1200px;">
                <div style="max-width: 800px;">
                    <p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Vice President • Haus Ally Supporting The Mother</p>
                    <h1 style="font-size: clamp(48px, 6vw, 72px); margin-bottom: 24px; color: white;">Vice President Ken</h1>
                    <p style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Supporting The Mother's executive leadership through allyship, resource redistribution, and amplifying trans women's voices in all haus governance decisions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Biography Section -->
        <section style="padding: var(--spacing-100) 0; background: var(--color-white);">
            <div class="container" style="max-width: 1200px;">
                <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 60px; align-items: start;">
                    <div>
                        <h2 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 32px;">About Vice President Ken</h2>

                        <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Vice President Ken Carson brings decades of experience in allyship, mutual aid organizing, and community care to the second-highest office in the land. His unwavering commitment to supporting President Barbie's vision of trans liberation while using his privilege to amplify marginalized voices has made him an invaluable partner in haus governance.</p>

                        <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Born and raised in Malibu, California, Ken developed a deep appreciation for solidarity and the importance of standing beside communities under attack. His journey toward authentic allyship began when he recognized how his privilege could be weaponized for liberation rather than maintaining oppressive systems.</p>

                        <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Throughout his career, Vice President Ken has dedicated himself to community defense, mutual aid networks, and protecting trans women—especially Black and Latina trans women who face the most violence. He understands that true allyship means taking direction from those most impacted, redistributing resources, and putting his body on the line when communities face threats.</p>

                        <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 24px;">As Vice President supporting The Mother's executive leadership, Ken coordinates between the Haus Council, The House (legislative branch), and The Elders (judicial branch). He chairs the Community Defense Council, leads mental health and harm reduction initiatives, and ensures resources flow to those who need them most. His role is to amplify, not overshadow - supporting trans women's leadership in all governance decisions.</p>

                        <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-top: 48px; margin-bottom: 24px;">Role in the Administration</h3>

                        <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Vice President Ken serves as President Barbie's closest advisor and trusted partner in liberation work. He chairs the Community Defense Council, oversees harm reduction and mental health initiatives, and represents the administration in solidarity networks both domestically and internationally. His portfolio includes building mutual aid infrastructure, supporting sex worker organizing, and ensuring resources reach ballroom and haus communities.</p>

                        <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Known for his commitment to authentic allyship, Ken has traveled extensively building relationships with trans-led organizations, sex worker collectives, and abolition movements. His "Community Care" tour centers the voices of those most impacted by state violence, ensuring that the administration's policies are shaped by those on the front lines of struggle rather than imposed from above.</p>

                        <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-top: 48px; margin-bottom: 24px;">Personal Life and Values</h3>

                        <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Vice President Ken is married to President Barbie, and their partnership—both personal and political—has been central to the administration's commitment to liberation. Together, they model how power can be shared, how allies can take direction from those most impacted, and how chosen family structures can challenge traditional hierarchies.</p>

                        <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Ken practices community care through harm reduction, mutual aid, and direct action. He believes strongly in redistributing resources and has made supporting grassroots organizing—particularly trans-led, sex worker-led, and BIPOC-led movements—a cornerstone of his vice presidency. He understands that wellness under capitalism requires collective resistance, not just individual self-care.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <div style="background: var(--color-cream); border: 2px solid var(--color-pale); border-radius: var(--radius-large); padding: 32px; position: sticky; top: 120px;">
                            <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-bottom: 24px; color: var(--color-text-dark);">Quick Facts</h3>

                            <div style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
                                <p style="font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: var(--color-text-dark); opacity: 0.7; margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 600;">Full Name</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0;">Kenneth Sean Carson</p>
                            </div>

                            <div style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
                                <p style="font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: var(--color-text-dark); opacity: 0.7; margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 600;">Born</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0;">March 11, 1961</p>
                            </div>

                            <div style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
                                <p style="font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: var(--color-text-dark); opacity: 0.7; margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 600;">Birthplace</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0;">Malibu, California</p>
                            </div>

                            <div style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
                                <p style="font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: var(--color-text-dark); opacity: 0.7; margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 600;">Spouse</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0;">President Barbie</p>
                            </div>

                            <div style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
                                <p style="font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: var(--color-text-dark); opacity: 0.7; margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 600;">Education</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0;">MBA, Public Policy Degree</p>
                            </div>

                            <div>
                                <p style="font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: var(--color-text-dark); opacity: 0.7; margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 600;">Coalition</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0;">Liberation Haus Coalition</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Initiatives -->
        <section style="padding: var(--spacing-100) 0; background: var(--color-light);">
            <div class="container" style="max-width: 1200px;">
                <h2 style="color: var(--color-primary); text-align: center; margin-bottom: 60px;">Key Initiatives</h2>

                <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 40px;">
                    <div style="background: var(--color-white); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border: 2px solid var(--color-pale);">
                        <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 16px;">Community Defense</h3>
                        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Leading the Community Defense Council to build mutual aid networks, organize safety patrols for trans women, and create alternatives to police violence.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: var(--color-white); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border: 2px solid var(--color-pale);">
                        <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 16px;">Harm Reduction & Mental Health</h3>
                        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Championing accessible mental health services, overdose prevention sites, and community care models that reject carceral approaches to wellness.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: var(--color-white); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border: 2px solid var(--color-pale);">
                        <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 16px;">Haus Infrastructure</h3>
                        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Ensuring chosen family structures receive the recognition, resources, and legal protections traditionally reserved for nuclear families.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: var(--color-white); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border: 2px solid var(--color-pale);">
                        <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 16px;">Economic Justice</h3>
                        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Partnering with worker cooperatives, sex worker collectives, and grassroots economic initiatives that build power outside capitalist exploitation.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: var(--color-white); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border: 2px solid var(--color-pale);">
                        <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 16px;">Solidarity Networks</h3>
                        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Building relationships with trans-led organizations, abolition movements, and international liberation struggles to ensure collective resistance.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: var(--color-white); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border: 2px solid var(--color-pale);">
                        <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 16px;">Resource Redistribution</h3>
                        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Directing state resources toward mutual aid, reparations, and grassroots organizing rather than policing and punishment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Inspirational Quotes -->
        <section style="padding: var(--spacing-100) 0; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-secondary) 0%, var(--color-primary-accent) 100%); color: white;">
            <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
                <h2 style="color: white; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 60px;">In His Own Words</h2>

                <div style="display: grid; gap: 40px;">
                    <blockquote style="background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold); margin: 0;">
                        <p style="font-size: 22px; font-family: var(--font-serif); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 16px;">"My role is to listen, take direction, and use my privilege to amplify the voices of those most impacted. Trans women, especially Black and Latina trans women, are leading this movement—I'm just here to help clear the path."</p>
                        <footer style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Vice Presidential Acceptance Speech</footer>
                    </blockquote>

                    <blockquote style="background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold); margin: 0;">
                        <p style="font-size: 22px; font-family: var(--font-serif); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 16px;">"Harm reduction saves lives. We need to stop criminalizing survival and start building community care systems that actually support people instead of punishing them."</p>
                        <footer style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Community Care Initiative Launch</footer>
                    </blockquote>

                    <blockquote style="background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold); margin: 0;">
                        <p style="font-size: 22px; font-family: var(--font-serif); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 16px;">"Our strength isn't measured by military might or GDP—it's measured by how we protect those most vulnerable to state violence, how we build mutual aid networks, and how we practice solidarity with liberation movements worldwide."</p>
                        <footer style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Community Defense Address</footer>
                    </blockquote>

                    <blockquote style="background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); padding: 40px; border-radius: var(--radius-large); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold); margin: 0;">
                        <p style="font-size: 22px; font-family: var(--font-serif); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 16px;">"True allyship means getting uncomfortable. It means redistributing resources, challenging systems that benefit me, and accepting that my role is to support—not lead—liberation movements."</p>
                        <footer style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Solidarity Summit</footer>
                    </blockquote>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

